recognizing and resolving

00:47:32.630 --> 00:47:35.860
the very serious
issues that we face.

00:47:35.860 --> 00:47:37.420
And I think a large
reason for that

00:47:37.420 --> 00:47:40.880
is because our populace as a
whole does not understand it.

00:47:40.880 --> 00:47:43.410
That's why we
conducted this survey.

00:47:43.410 --> 00:47:45.160
It's just a random
survey of young people.

00:47:45.160 --> 00:47:46.784
What do you know
about nuclear weapons?

00:47:46.784 --> 00:47:50.340
And the answer is abysmal,
abysmal ignorance.

00:47:50.340 --> 00:47:55.560
And along with the
ignorance, not much concern.

00:47:55.560 --> 00:48:00.680
So if we're really going to get
sensible policies for dealing

00:48:00.680 --> 00:48:04.360
with the dangers which
we're waving our arms about,

00:48:04.360 --> 00:48:06.110
you can wave your arms
about all you want,

00:48:06.110 --> 00:48:07.485
but you have got
to have policies

00:48:07.485 --> 00:48:10.100
to correct the problems.

00:48:10.100 --> 00:48:12.870
We have to find a way
of educating people,

00:48:12.870 --> 00:48:17.470
particularly educating
young people, on this issue.

00:48:17.470 --> 00:48:21.700
The kids you saw
in that video not

00:48:21.700 --> 00:48:24.460
only didn't know
about the Cold War,

00:48:24.460 --> 00:48:26.850
they didn't even
know about 9/11.

00:48:26.850 --> 00:48:31.640
So this is a grossly
uninformed population.

00:48:31.640 --> 00:48:34.510
And so we we're setting
out an educational program

00:48:34.510 --> 00:48:36.600
to try to deal
with that problem,

00:48:36.600 --> 00:48:39.630
and an education program
directed primarily

00:48:39.630 --> 00:48:42.770
at young adults.

00:48:42.770 --> 00:48:47.380
We believe that the
reason our policies are

00:48:47.380 --> 00:48:51.650
so inadequate today-- let me
back up and say more directly.

00:48:51.650 --> 00:48:54.360
A complete declarative
statement is

00:48:54.360 --> 00:48:57.950
that the danger of a
nuclear catastrophe today

00:48:57.950 --> 00:48:59.450
of one of the kinds
we talked about,

00:48:59.450 --> 00:49:01.830
the danger of a
catastrophe today

00:49:01.830 --> 00:49:05.370
is greater than it was
during the Cold War.

00:49:05.370 --> 00:49:07.450
It is greater than it
was during the Cold War.

00:49:07.450 --> 00:49:09.250
We've documented that
several various ways.

00:49:09.250 --> 00:49:11.880
I talk about it in
great detail in my book.

00:49:11.880 --> 00:49:14.696
And I'm just writing another
paper now, dealing specifically

00:49:14.696 --> 00:49:16.320
with it, why I believe
that to be true,

00:49:16.320 --> 00:49:18.967
and how I can document it, why
I believe it is an accurate

00:49:18.967 --> 00:49:19.800
way of assessing it.

00:49:23.090 --> 00:49:25.970
If it's greater today,
it's also perfectly clear

00:49:25.970 --> 00:49:28.340
that our policies are
not adequate for dealing

00:49:28.340 --> 00:49:29.370
with those dangers.

00:49:29.370 --> 00:49:31.960
We're blissfully going
ahead, both we and Russia,

00:49:31.960 --> 00:49:35.430
rebuilding the Cold
War nuclear arsenal.

00:49:35.430 --> 00:49:37.940
Never mind the $1 trillion
cost associated with it,

00:49:37.940 --> 00:49:41.980
the dangers associated with
that are very, very real.

00:49:41.980 --> 00:49:45.500
So we need a program
of education.

00:49:45.500 --> 00:49:50.504
You can't rant about policies
if you don't understand

00:49:50.504 --> 00:49:51.420
the underlying issues.

00:49:51.420 --> 00:49:53.550
So the first step
is education, and it

00:49:53.550 --> 00:49:58.330
has to be some kind
of a mass education.

00:49:58.330 --> 00:50:00.950
So sure, I teach a course
at Stanford on this subject.

00:50:00.950 --> 00:50:03.870
I get a couple hundred
students, which is nice,

00:50:03.870 --> 00:50:06.414
but that doesn't influence
what's going on in the world.

00:50:06.414 --> 00:50:08.330
I had to find a way of
getting the information

00:50:08.330 --> 00:50:10.480
through to hundreds of
thousands of students,

00:50:10.480 --> 00:50:13.260
or even millions
of young people.

00:50:13.260 --> 00:50:17.240
And so, obviously, the internet
is the only way to do that.

00:50:17.240 --> 00:50:20.090
And we're trying in our
project to put together

00:50:20.090 --> 00:50:23.680
media that can work, that can
be effective over the internet,

00:50:23.680 --> 00:50:25.930
and which will attract young
people to read it and get

00:50:25.930 --> 00:50:26.596
engaged with it.

00:50:30.020 --> 00:50:32.580
One of the reasons I'm happy
to talk with this group today

00:50:32.580 --> 00:50:34.600
is we need help with
what we're doing,

00:50:34.600 --> 00:50:38.530
and certainly no one ought
to be better qualified

00:50:38.530 --> 00:50:41.060
on how to effectively
use the internet

00:50:41.060 --> 00:50:44.050
to communicate with millions
of people than people here

00:50:44.050 --> 00:50:45.747
at Google.

00:50:45.747 --> 00:50:48.080
So we're in our own fumbling
way doing these things now.

00:50:48.080 --> 00:50:50.350
We're preparing videos,
